Name as Parent - this is a special case of NameAsOther that uses the lexical parent of a nested object as the target object. (The lexical parent is the enclosing object in a nested object definition; in other words, it's the object in which the nested object is embedded.) `class `**`NameAsParent`**` :   `[`NameAsOther`](../object/NameAsOther.html)
